casebody.data:
Harry HENRY, Appellant, v. METROPOLITAN TRUST COMPANY, Girlie Strosnider and R. N. Strosnider, Appellees. No. 7417. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 21, 1934. I. Henry Harris, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Frank S. Hutton, of Los Angolés, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges, and NORCROSS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellees, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
